        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 10:30PM MDT until June 27 at 11:00PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 1028 PM MDT/1128 PM CDT/, a severe thunderstorm was located 9
miles southwest of Brewster, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Goodland, Brewster, and Edson.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 15 and 46.

The National Weather Service in Goodland received 1 inch of rain in
30 minutes, in addition to half inch hail and wind gusts up to 59
mph.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of
a building.

Torrential rainfall with this storm may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
